  title: Garden
  description: 'Gardens at country estates served both practical and aesthetic purposes.
    They were used to grow herbs, vegetables, and sometimes fruit, supporting household
    needs. At the same time, gardens were carefully designed to demonstrate control
    over nature and reflect the wealth and status of the estate owner. '
